texts.text: ...Hey.
Hello?!
You all alone, kid?
You all alone, kid?
Then I can stay with you if you want.
>That was how you met your new demon companion.
>A world destroyed by a rain of ICBMs.
>It is but one of the many fates that await you.
>One of the many alternate futures that may come to be, depending on the choices you make.
[sys user_name]!
What is it?
I hear you.
Look over there. The sky's pretty dark there.
Does that mean it might rain?
What? Don't give me that look.
You think you're too good to be troubled by trivial stuff like the weather or something?
Then don't take forever to respond goddammit!
And you always have this annoyed look on your face.
It's not nice!
>Probably fed up with your attitude,
>Pixie circles the air in agitation...
>You hear the sound of feet stepping on ground.
>You look towards the direction of the noise and see...
I've finally found you, [sys user_name].
You've been living in hiding here all these years?
Who's this dude?
Is he your friend, [sys user_name]?
Hi there, little one.
Are you [sys user_name]'s demon?
What the...?!
>Pixie hides herself behind you, peeking out warily...
What the hell is going on...? I'm getting some strange vibes from this guy...
Looks like I've upset her.
It's been a long time, [sys user_name]. Glad to see you again.
Leave me alone.
I'm not talking to you.
It seems the little one's not the only one I've upset.
...But I suppose I deserve to be treated like this.
You betrayed the Liberators to fight beside me and the Acolytes,
all for the sake of saving the world from destruction.
But we ended up failing. Your disenchanted seclusion here is understandable.
>You glare at Jabo in silence.
Please don't stare at me like that.
I did not search far and wide for you just to pick a fight.
There's something I need to tell you. It won't take long.
Do you know what caused the destruction of this world?
It was Vanitas.
It was my fault.
Yes.
[sys user_name]...?
You feel guilty.
Sorry to put a damper on your self loathing,
but I was talking about the actual phenomenon that caused the destruction.
In short, the destruction of the world was due to Vanitas being activated.
When Vanitas was activated, it brought destruction upon the world.
But how was Vanitas activated?
>You stare in silence at Jabo for a moment, then you say
>"Because we weren't able to suppress human malice."
Yes. Like you said, the spread of human malice was such that
Vanitas awakened way faster than I anticipated.
We underestimated Vanitas,
therefor we have to take responsibility for failing to save the world from destruction.
That's what you think right? I thought the same.
But what if...
What if someone staged all this? What would you think?
What do you mean by that?
Everything's too late now anyway.
Yes, it probably sounds like an excuse now that the world has been shattered.
But what if it's true? Think about it.
What if someone fooled even me and secretly brought about
this world's destruction on purpose? Are you going to let that go?
And when I realized this fact, I thought to myself
"There is still a way to save the survivors of this shattered world."
Now, [sys user_name]. Let me ask you once more.
Do you know what caused the destruction of this world?
If you want to find out the truth, then travel the world.
Oh, but...
This world... It has become a living hell to humans.
So prepare yourself well before you set out on your journey.
Well then. I have said what I came here to say, now I will take my leave...
I myself have things that I must do.
>Jabo looks into your eyes and smiles.
[sys user_name].
I still want to save the humans, the ones that survived at least.
I'm not asking you to give me an answer right now,
but I hope we can work together again once more when you've seen the world we are in now.
See you around, [sys user_name].
>Jabo raises his hand slightly in farewell and leaves.
...He's gone.
Hey [sys user_name], who was that guy?
Just an old acquaintance.
A friend.
Acquaintance...? So you're not friends?
...Can he be trusted?
I mean, is he really even human?
He felt like an extremely powerful demon... Are you listening?!
Oh, he's your friend?
...Really? You're not kidding me are you?
Aren't people usually more happy when they meet a friend... Are you listening?
I'm still talking here you know, pay attention!
>You reply to Pixie's outburst absently
>as you check on your life supplies.
>...You are a bit short, but it isn't that serious.
We used up quite a lot...
Supplies are hard to come by these days, so I guess it couldn't be helped...
Should we go look for supplies somewhere?
Yeah.
Let's go.
Okay, then tomorrow we'll...
Huh? N-Now?! We're going right now?!
Hey! Wait up! I'm coming with you!
